title: World News: Olympian Who Got Visa Won't Go Home
text:
"I was just afraid for my life, afraid to go to jail," Ms. Tsimanouskaya said. "I don't think I can ever go back to Belarus."

On Sunday, members of the Belarusian team in Tokyo took Ms. Tsimanouskaya to the airport in an attempt to send her home after she publicly criticized the country's Olympic coaches. Ms. Tsimanouskaya didn't board the flight and appealed to the International Olympic Committee for help.

She said she was looking to continue her athletic career abroad and is looking ahead to the next Olympics: Paris 2024.
